# Market Quantitative Analytics

Exploring techniques and algorithms used in **Quantitative Analytics.**
Answeres for the **Market Quantitative Analytics simulation** from forage.com

## Overview
This project explores the tasks in the **Market Quantitative Analytics simulation** from forage.com. The documents are:
| Documents | Description |
| :--- | :--- |
| `twoFuturesContract.py` | Parameterised to accept user inputted values. Will calculate cost-of-carry, Black-Scholes Model, and Monte Carlo Simulations |
| futuresContractOuput | Output of the `twoFuturesContract.py` given the values provided in the **Market Quantitative Analytics simulation** |
| fourRiskManagementAnalysis | Methods for management of risk given varied situations |

## Requirements
'''
python
numpy
scipy
argparse
'''

## Example Usage
```bash
python twoFuturesContract.py \
  --spotPrice <value> \
  --rate <value> \
  --storage <value> \
  --timeToMaturity <value> \
  --strikePrice <value> \
  --volatility <value>
```

### Parameter Descriptions

* `spotPrice` – Current price of coffee
* `rate` – Current risk free rate as a decimalised percentage per annum
* `storage` – Current cost of storage as a decimalised percentage per annum
* `timeToMaturity` – Time for contract to mature in months
* `strikePrice` – Strike price for the commodity
* `volatility` – olitility as a decimilised percentage

## Project Goals

* Calculate the cost-of-carry, Black-Scholes, and Monte Carlo Simulation on user given values
